                            <comment id="117854" author="di.wang" created="Tue, 9 Jun 2015 00:24:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, this is expected. LWP(light weight proxy) is not a replayable client, so it will never get into recovery mode. But OSP is a replayable client, which will always enter into recovery mode when required.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="117816" author="simmonsja" created="Mon, 8 Jun 2015 23:40:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In my testing I noticed end after a cleanup shut down of the file system when the file system is restarted all the MDS servers go into recovery with each other. The lwp layers reconnect fine without going into recovery but the OSP layer always enters recovery mode. Is this  the excepted behavior?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
